課程概述 Course Description
       一、教學內容：本學科將提供藝術學學生藝術學的研究概論與其實際運用。授課的主要講題將著重於圖像學、維也納學派、歷史文獻與圖像之相互關聯、形式主義、社會藝術史和這個學科領域的相關問題。我們將針對各學派與學者們的研究方法與藝術學所衍生的各式問題進行研究與瞭解。二、教學進度：（一）藝術學與藝術史學研究方法論；形式主義─弗萊；圖像學：渥伯格研究所、潘諾夫斯基(E.Panofsky)圖像學研究法、貢布里西；渥夫林“藝術的原則”；渥林格的“抽象與移情”；藝術社會學史─亞諾•豪索、安大略。This course seeks to give the advanced art history student an overview of the history and use of art historical methodology. Addressing such key issues as iconography, Vienna School of Art History, the relationship between the image and historical documentation, Formalism, social art history and other central problems in the field, we will attempt to explain these issues and methods as themselves subject to the historical conditions of the academy and the individual authors. Methodology Art Research and Art Historical Methodology. Formalism─Roger Fry. Iconography─The Warburg Institute,Erwin Panofsky, Ernst H. Gombrich. Heinrich Woefflin, "Principles of Art History". Wilhelm Worringer─Abstraktion und einfuhlung. social art history─ Arnold Hauser、Frederick Antal.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
增加學生藝術理論學理基礎著重理論與實際之相互配合運用拓展具前瞻性的學術議題 

